  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat.",
    "2. Cut the datterini tomatoes in half and brush with sesame oil.",
    "3. Season the tomatoes with salt and Korean chili flakes.",
    "4. Grill the tomatoes for 3-4 minutes per side, or until they develop a charred exterior.",
    "5. In a small bowl, whisk together gochujang, brown sugar, and 1 tablespoon of water.",
    "6. Once the tomatoes are grilled, brush the gochujang glaze over them.",
    "7. Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve immediately."
